WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:08.299 --> 00:00:09.717
<i>Dr. Al?</i>

2
00:00:11.970 --> 00:00:13.179
Dr. Al.

3
00:00:15.515 --> 00:00:17.392
Trauma's at the back door.

4
00:00:22.856 --> 00:00:25.233
Let me know when the rest
of her labs are back.

5
00:00:27.652 --> 00:00:29.945
The girlfriend
hasn't been much help.

6
00:00:29.946 --> 00:00:32.948
- Is she being uncooperative?
- No. not really.

7
00:00:32.949 --> 00:00:34.950
{\an8}Apparently. she's only been
going out

8
00:00:34.951 --> 00:00:36.952
{\an8}with the little girl Kylie's
father for a few months.

9
00:00:36.953 --> 00:00:40.080
{\an8}- Where is he now?
- He's in New Castle for work.

10
00:00:40.081 --> 00:00:41.957
{\an8}I left him a message
to come in.

11
00:00:41.958 --> 00:00:43.959
Okay. come find me
when he gets here.

12
00:00:43.960 --> 00:00:45.711
You talk to
the trauma counselor this week?

13
00:00:45.712 --> 00:00:47.337
I'm going to.

14
00:00:47.338 --> 00:00:48.881
Promise.
- Okay. good.

15
00:00:48.882 --> 00:00:50.674
- Medics are rolling in.
- I'll be right there.

16
00:00:50.675 --> 00:00:52.968
How's our little girl
who took a stair tumble?

17
00:00:52.969 --> 00:00:54.970
I'm going to check
for internal hemorrhage

18
00:00:54.971 --> 00:00:56.472
with an ultrasound.

19
00:00:56.473 --> 00:00:58.390
- What is your gut telling you?
- Her gut?

20
00:00:58.391 --> 00:01:01.351
Yeah. it's this thing
that AI will never have.

21
00:01:01.352 --> 00:01:02.978
I don't want to think

22
00:01:02.979 --> 00:01:05.189
about what my gut is saying
right now.

23
00:01:05.190 --> 00:01:06.982
Come find me
when you know more.

24
00:01:06.983 --> 00:01:08.817
- Us. if you don't mind.
- I don't mind.

25
00:01:08.818 --> 00:01:10.319
Us--come find us
when you know more.

26
00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:11.904
Do you want to jump
on this trauma?

27
00:01:11.905 --> 00:01:13.405
I've got my hands full.

28
00:01:13.406 --> 00:01:14.990
I don't want this one
getting away from me.

29
00:01:14.991 --> 00:01:16.408
We don't know
what this is yet.

30
00:01:16.409 --> 00:01:17.993
Don't go jumping
to conclusions.

31
00:01:17.994 --> 00:01:19.411
I'm not jumping to anything.

32
00:01:19.412 --> 00:01:21.497
I'm just looking out
for my patient.

33
00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:26.335
Uh. something I should know
about Santos?

34
00:01:26.336 --> 00:01:29.004
Very confident. not afraid
to get her hands dirty.

35
00:01:29.005 --> 00:01:30.422
strong patient advocate. fearless.

36
00:01:30.423 --> 00:01:32.216
Seems like
you were suggesting

37
00:01:32.217 --> 00:01:34.009
she jumps to conclusions.
- No. no. no. no.

38
00:01:34.010 --> 00:01:36.011
I was merely suggesting
or reminding her not to.

39
00:01:36.012 --> 00:01:38.013
Yeah.
- Uh. 58-year-old guy.

40
00:01:38.014 --> 00:01:39.848
Tripped with
a scaphoid fracture.

41
00:01:39.849 --> 00:01:43.352
Epistaxis. non-focal neuro.
but denies head trauma.

42
00:01:43.353 --> 00:01:44.645
But every time I check on him.

43
00:01:44.646 --> 00:01:46.897
his affect
has drastically changed.

44
00:01:46.898 --> 00:01:49.942
My gut is telling me
something's not right.

45
00:01:53.029 --> 00:01:54.655
What?
- Nothing.

46
00:01:54.656 --> 00:01:55.948
Your play.

47
00:01:55.949 --> 00:01:57.449
Start with a head CT.

48
00:01:57.450 --> 00:01:59.076
If normal. LP.
rule out encephalitis.

49
00:01:59.077 --> 00:02:00.619
Put in your orders.

50
00:02:00.620 --> 00:02:02.079
Has he been here before?
- No.

51
00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:03.872
Have you called
the family to rule out

52
00:02:03.873 --> 00:02:05.874
any psychiatric history?
- No. but I will.

53
00:02:05.875 --> 00:02:07.876
Do you want to jump
on this trauma in the meantime?

54
00:02:07.877 --> 00:02:09.378
- What is it?
- It's a surprise.

55
00:02:09.379 --> 00:02:10.463
Wonderful.

56
00:02:12.924 --> 00:02:14.842
Mel. you want to jump
on this?

57
00:02:14.843 --> 00:02:17.052
- What is it?
- It's a surprise.

58
00:02:17.053 --> 00:02:18.679
What do you got
for us. Amboy?

59
00:02:18.680 --> 00:02:20.848
Allen Billings--
Pallet of roofing tiles

60
00:02:20.849 --> 00:02:24.143
fell eight feet. hit his upper
arm with an open dislocation.

61
00:02:24.144 --> 00:02:25.727
Ouch.

62
00:02:25.728 --> 00:02:27.729
Two rounds of fent.
1 then 0.5 per kilo.

63
00:02:27.730 --> 00:02:29.273
A and O. with good vitals.

64
00:02:29.274 --> 00:02:31.608
- Mel. hold the arm steady.
- Sure.

65
00:02:31.609 --> 00:02:33.652
<i>Uno. dos. tres.</i>

66
00:02:35.071 --> 00:02:37.072
Mr. Billings. I'm Dr. McKay.

67
00:02:37.073 --> 00:02:38.782
And I'm Dr. Garcia
from surgery.

68
00:02:38.783 --> 00:02:40.742
- And this is Dr. King.
- Hi.

69
00:02:40.743 --> 00:02:42.286
- Oh. it really hurts.
- Give us a minute.

70
00:02:42.287 --> 00:02:43.996
And we're gonna take care
of that. okay?

71
00:02:43.997 --> 00:02:45.706
Any headache.
chest or belly pain?

72
00:02:45.707 --> 00:02:47.958
- No. just the arm.
- Sats 99. Pulse 104.

73
00:02:47.959 --> 00:02:49.501
BP 116/78.

74
00:02:49.502 --> 00:02:50.836
What do you think. Dr. King?

75
00:02:50.837 --> 00:02:53.088
Oh. um. it is
an open dislocation.

76
00:02:53.089 --> 00:02:55.507
Can you be more specific?

77
00:02:55.508 --> 00:02:57.801
I think it's inferior. yeah?

78
00:02:57.802 --> 00:03:00.637
Do you remember
the name for that?

79
00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:05.767
Sounds like
a Harry Potter spell.

80
00:03:05.768 --> 00:03:08.979
- I...
- Luxatio erecta.

81
00:03:08.980 --> 00:03:10.981
Correct.
Check the neuro-circ.

82
00:03:10.982 --> 00:03:13.108
Sir. can you feel me
touching you?

83
00:03:13.109 --> 00:03:14.651
Okay.

84
00:03:14.652 --> 00:03:17.446
Can you wiggle your fingers?
- Yeah.

85
00:03:17.447 --> 00:03:20.407
- Good radial pulse.
- E-FAST is negative.

86
00:03:20.408 --> 00:03:24.328
- Okay. what's next. Dr. McKay?
- Ancef and gentamicin.

87
00:03:24.329 --> 00:03:26.747
Sedate for traction. countertraction.

88
00:03:26.748 --> 00:03:29.333
And he needs a CT angiogram
to rule out vascular injury.

89
00:03:29.334 --> 00:03:30.834
That sounds like a plan.

90
00:03:30.835 --> 00:03:32.169
But with an open joint.
he needs a washout

91
00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:33.795
in the OR with ortho.
- Agreed.

92
00:03:33.796 --> 00:03:35.505
Instead of wasting
time down here.

93
00:03:35.506 --> 00:03:38.133
it should be easier to reduce
under general anesthesia

94
00:03:38.134 --> 00:03:40.135
with fewer risks.
- Possibly.

95
00:03:40.136 --> 00:03:41.970
Let's get
an opinion from ortho.

96
00:03:43.389 --> 00:03:45.390
You're definitely new.
Doctor--wishful thinking.

97
00:03:45.391 --> 00:03:47.059
Ortho like to take
their sweet time.

98
00:03:47.060 --> 00:03:48.894
Okay. sedation orders.
Dr. McKay.

99
00:03:48.895 --> 00:03:50.979
100 of propofol.
Titrate to effect.

100
00:03:50.980 --> 00:03:52.689
Be back with that.

101
00:03:52.690 --> 00:03:53.983
Excuse me.

102
00:03:57.570 --> 00:04:00.614
- How's your day going. Doc?
- Yeah. pretty good.

103
00:04:00.615 --> 00:04:03.534
Looks like
your albumin's infusing.

104
00:04:05.828 --> 00:04:08.580
Oh. uh. medical students
Ogilvie and Kwon

105
00:04:08.581 --> 00:04:09.706
are gonna be working with me.

106
00:04:09.707 --> 00:04:11.333
- Hello.
- Student doctors.

107
00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:12.751
You want them to try it?

108
00:04:12.752 --> 00:04:14.711
They got to learn sometime.

109
00:04:14.712 --> 00:04:17.172
Uh. it's best if they watch
the first one.

110
00:04:17.173 --> 00:04:18.882
- I can prep and drape.
- Yeah.

111
00:04:18.883 --> 00:04:22.386
- After your albumin's in.
- That's correct.

112
00:04:22.387 --> 00:04:24.972
Uh. to prevent hypotension.
we introduce albumin

113
00:04:24.973 --> 00:04:27.599
if we anticipate
more than five liters.

114
00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:29.101
Last time it was six.

115
00:04:29.102 --> 00:04:31.645
That's. like.
a gallon and a half.

116
00:04:31.646 --> 00:04:34.439
Of high-octane premium.

117
00:04:34.440 --> 00:04:36.400
Okay. you need
anything else. Mr. Louie?

118
00:04:36.401 --> 00:04:37.693
- No. ma'am.
- Okay.

119
00:04:37.694 --> 00:04:39.903
Grab me when you're ready?
- Yeah.

120
00:04:39.904 --> 00:04:43.031
Whitaker. wife of your DNR
this morning is in Central 8.

121
00:04:43.032 --> 00:04:45.033
Does she know
her husband died?

122
00:04:45.034 --> 00:04:47.202
Not till you tell her.

123
00:04:47.203 --> 00:04:48.620
I'll be right there.

124
00:04:48.621 --> 00:04:52.457
Uh. yeah. uh. always make sure

125
00:04:52.458 --> 00:04:54.251
your entry point is safe

126
00:04:54.252 --> 00:04:56.295
by identifying the pocket
of fluid.

127
00:04:56.296 --> 00:04:58.213
That's not a pocket.
That's a lake.

128
00:04:58.214 --> 00:05:00.090
Yeah. but you do not want
to hit a vein or artery

129
00:05:00.091 --> 00:05:02.592
on the way in. so make sure
you check with color Doppler.

130
00:05:02.593 --> 00:05:04.970
Huh.

131
00:05:04.971 --> 00:05:06.555
Joy?

132
00:05:06.556 --> 00:05:08.932
I can't see.
I can't see anything.

133
00:05:08.933 --> 00:05:10.559
That's 'cause your eye
is shut.

134
00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:11.893
I can't open it.
It's glued shut.

135
00:05:11.894 --> 00:05:13.729
I was trying to put on lashes.

136
00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:17.232
Oh. my God.
Am I gonna go blind?

137
00:05:17.233 --> 00:05:19.234
No. no. I'm pretty sure
this is something we can fix.

138
00:05:19.235 --> 00:05:21.237
Just take a deep breath.

139
00:05:22.697 --> 00:05:26.867
Okay. so you. uh. glued your
eye shut with what exactly?

140
00:05:26.868 --> 00:05:28.410
- Super glue.
- Okay.

141
00:05:28.411 --> 00:05:30.120
Well. is it something
you typically use

142
00:05:30.121 --> 00:05:31.538
to apply your lashes?

143
00:05:31.539 --> 00:05:33.248
No. it's typically
something you use

144
00:05:33.249 --> 00:05:35.125
to glue shit you break.
like coffee mugs and stuff.

145
00:05:35.126 --> 00:05:36.918
You know
what I'm talking about.

146
00:05:36.919 --> 00:05:39.504
It's--it's--it's super glue.
- Okay. okay. Yeah. got it.

147
00:05:39.505 --> 00:05:41.506
Can I just talk to Dr. J?

148
00:05:41.507 --> 00:05:43.300
She'll know what to do.

149
00:05:43.301 --> 00:05:45.260
Is that an ophthalmologist?

150
00:05:45.261 --> 00:05:47.637
No. she works here in the ER.

151
00:05:47.638 --> 00:05:49.264
Yeah. I don't think so.

152
00:05:49.265 --> 00:05:51.266
But I know what I'm doing...

153
00:05:51.267 --> 00:05:52.727
most of the time.

154
00:05:55.480 --> 00:05:58.482
For a Z-track.
we pull up the skin

155
00:05:58.483 --> 00:06:02.069
before advancing
into the peritoneal space.

156
00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:04.738
- Looks good.
- Fluid's clear.

157
00:06:04.739 --> 00:06:06.865
Does that hurt
as much as it looks?

158
00:06:06.866 --> 00:06:09.493
Oh. it's not too bad.

159
00:06:09.494 --> 00:06:11.453
Ogilvie. spike
the bottle for me.

160
00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:13.663
What tests do we
want on these fluids?

161
00:06:13.664 --> 00:06:15.457
Uh. Cell count
to rule out spontaneous

162
00:06:15.458 --> 00:06:16.958
bacterial peritonitis.
- Ding.

163
00:06:16.959 --> 00:06:19.044
What would make
that diagnosis. Joy?

164
00:06:19.045 --> 00:06:20.629
Um...

165
00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:22.339
Absolute neutrophil count
over 250.

166
00:06:23.966 --> 00:06:27.511
- How are we doing in here?
- They are doing great.

167
00:06:27.512 --> 00:06:29.222
I think they got this.

168
00:06:33.059 --> 00:06:34.935
Hey. Dana. can you get
Kiara down here for me?

169
00:06:34.936 --> 00:06:36.728
She isn't answering
her Spectralink.

170
00:06:36.729 --> 00:06:39.314
She's not working today.
It's. uh...

171
00:06:39.315 --> 00:06:41.066
I forget. I'll find out
and get 'em down here.

172
00:06:41.067 --> 00:06:42.567
What else you need?

173
00:06:42.568 --> 00:06:45.320
How about
a double espresso martini?

174
00:06:45.321 --> 00:06:47.823
I like the way you think.

175
00:06:47.824 --> 00:06:50.534
Hey. Trudy. it's Dana.
What's going on up there?

176
00:06:50.535 --> 00:06:52.202
What's up. Crash?

177
00:06:52.203 --> 00:06:55.205
You mean besides
my mother driving me insane?

178
00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:58.542
Just tell her that her
efforts would be better suited

179
00:06:58.543 --> 00:07:00.961
endorsing someone like myself.

180
00:07:00.962 --> 00:07:04.464
If you're seriously thinking
of a double residency.

181
00:07:04.465 --> 00:07:07.342
let me save you the trouble--
you can't do it.

182
00:07:07.343 --> 00:07:10.178
Why? Just because you
couldn't do it?

183
00:07:10.179 --> 00:07:13.181
Honestly. yes.

184
00:07:13.182 --> 00:07:15.767
Because you're a genius.

185
00:07:15.768 --> 00:07:17.185
Yes.

186
00:07:17.186 --> 00:07:19.020
What's the square root
of 841?

187
00:07:19.021 --> 00:07:21.022
I'm not a human calculator.

188
00:07:21.023 --> 00:07:22.691
Social worker
Dylan Easton is covering

189
00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:24.109
for Kiara this weekend.

190
00:07:24.110 --> 00:07:25.986
They're on their way down.
- Thank you.

191
00:07:25.987 --> 00:07:27.028
Yep.

192
00:07:27.029 --> 00:07:28.655
Oh. shit.

193
00:07:28.656 --> 00:07:30.740
I have a nun
with conjunctivitis.

194
00:07:30.741 --> 00:07:32.075
Her swab is showing

195
00:07:32.076 --> 00:07:33.910
gram-negative
intracellular diplococci.

196
00:07:33.911 --> 00:07:35.245
Gonorrhea?

197
00:07:35.246 --> 00:07:37.581
Come to Jesus.

198
00:07:37.582 --> 00:07:39.749
Well. the lab--the lab
must have made a mistake.

199
00:07:39.750 --> 00:07:42.127
Maybe it's
an immaculate infection.

200
00:07:42.128 --> 00:07:44.045
I'll call the lab supe.
clear this up.

201
00:07:44.046 --> 00:07:45.589
Tread carefully. missy.

202
00:07:45.590 --> 00:07:49.302
There's a nun
with gonorrhea in her eye.

203
00:07:51.387 --> 00:07:53.805
Seriously. you guys are gonna
take this away from me?

204
00:07:53.806 --> 00:07:55.724
I'm disappointed in you two.

205
00:07:55.725 --> 00:07:57.267
29.

206
00:07:57.268 --> 00:07:58.602
What?

207
00:07:58.603 --> 00:08:00.937
The square root of 841.

208
00:08:00.938 --> 00:08:02.772
How we doing with Mr. Digby?

209
00:08:02.773 --> 00:08:04.608
He's in a gown in South 21.

210
00:08:04.609 --> 00:08:06.610
Is there someplace
we can get this laundered?

211
00:08:06.611 --> 00:08:08.612
Those are going
right in the incinerator.

212
00:08:08.613 --> 00:08:10.405
We'll get him
a whole new wardrobe.

213
00:08:10.406 --> 00:08:12.240
You ever use a cast saw before?
- Uh...

214
00:08:12.241 --> 00:08:14.409
Of course you haven't.
Well. today's your lucky day.

215
00:08:14.410 --> 00:08:15.911
Follow me.

216
00:08:15.912 --> 00:08:18.413
Dr. Mohan. you got a minute?
- Yeah.

217
00:08:18.414 --> 00:08:21.666
Have you met Emma?
First day. New grad RN.

218
00:08:21.667 --> 00:08:23.251
- Hi.
- Nice to meet you.

219
00:08:23.252 --> 00:08:25.170
Emma needs to learn
cast removal.

220
00:08:25.171 --> 00:08:26.838
How long has
the cast been on?

221
00:08:26.839 --> 00:08:28.632
Months. maybe years.

222
00:08:28.633 --> 00:08:30.509
Probably gonna want to breathe
through your mouth.

223
00:08:33.304 --> 00:08:35.430
All right. Mr. Digby.

224
00:08:35.431 --> 00:08:38.183
Dr. Mohan can cut
your cast off now.

225
00:08:38.184 --> 00:08:39.851
How long's the cast been on?

226
00:08:39.852 --> 00:08:42.729
I don't know.
but it's really getting itchy.

227
00:08:42.730 --> 00:08:45.440
{\an8}Okay. this cuts the cast...

228
00:08:45.441 --> 00:08:47.108
{\an8}Not the skin.

229
00:08:47.109 --> 00:08:49.487
This should relieve
the itching.

230
00:08:51.000 --> 00:08:57.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

231
00:09:02.291 --> 00:09:05.127
- Get the cast spreader.
- Oh. uh...

232
00:09:10.216 --> 00:09:13.301
Thank you.

233
00:09:13.302 --> 00:09:15.053
Okay.

234
00:09:18.891 --> 00:09:20.601
Okay.

235
00:09:25.481 --> 00:09:27.649
Oh. I see you
brought some friends.

236
00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:29.860
- Oh. my God. are those--
- Maggots.

237
00:09:35.491 --> 00:09:38.535
I'll need ethyl chloride spray
to freeze them off.

238
00:09:38.536 --> 00:09:41.330
Never saw that
in nursing school. am I right?

239
00:09:46.544 --> 00:09:49.087
Now irrigate like hell. Mel.

240
00:09:49.088 --> 00:09:50.131
Okay.

241
00:09:54.677 --> 00:09:56.803
Okay. on my count.

242
00:09:56.804 --> 00:10:00.765
One. two. three.

243
00:10:00.766 --> 00:10:02.767
Come on. motherfucker.

244
00:10:02.768 --> 00:10:04.686
Humeral head is not reducing.

245
00:10:04.687 --> 00:10:06.938
- Should be done in the OR.
- I am the OR.

246
00:10:06.939 --> 00:10:08.440
Okay. we're gonna get
this back in

247
00:10:08.441 --> 00:10:10.358
before ortho
even answers the page.

248
00:10:10.359 --> 00:10:12.944
Mel. stick four fingers
under that humeral head.

249
00:10:12.945 --> 00:10:14.279
Really?

250
00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:16.197
Yeah. get in there
really. really deep.

251
00:10:16.198 --> 00:10:19.034
And when you feel the traction
and lift it above the glenoid.

252
00:10:19.035 --> 00:10:21.036
that will convert this
to an anterior dislocation.

253
00:10:21.037 --> 00:10:23.371
and it should pop
right back in.

254
00:10:23.372 --> 00:10:25.206
Okay.

255
00:10:25.207 --> 00:10:26.541
Ready to go.

256
00:10:26.542 --> 00:10:29.878
One. two. three.

257
00:10:29.879 --> 00:10:31.713
Okay.

258
00:10:31.714 --> 00:10:33.965
- Ooh.
- Oh. very cool.

259
00:10:33.966 --> 00:10:36.176
Sterile saline dressing.

260
00:10:36.177 --> 00:10:38.637
- Shoulder immobilizer and CT.
- Okay.

261
00:10:38.638 --> 00:10:40.931
Guess you guys
don't need me anymore.

262
00:10:43.184 --> 00:10:45.852
- You all right. Dr. King?
- Yeah.

263
00:10:45.853 --> 00:10:48.355
You don't seem all right.

264
00:10:48.356 --> 00:10:50.774
Well. my deposition is today.

265
00:10:50.775 --> 00:10:53.151
Ah. do you want to talk
about it?

266
00:10:53.152 --> 00:10:54.819
I'm not allowed to.

267
00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:56.780
No. we don't have to talk
about the deposition.

268
00:10:56.781 --> 00:10:59.449
but we can talk
about how it is affecting you.

269
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:00.867
Average emergency physician

270
00:11:00.868 --> 00:11:02.744
catches a med-mal case
every seven years.

271
00:11:02.745 --> 00:11:04.579
Nine times out of ten.
the doctor wins.

272
00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:06.247
I've been sued
four times myself.

273
00:11:06.248 --> 00:11:08.583
Dr. Al?

274
00:11:08.584 --> 00:11:11.253
I've never been named
in a lawsuit.

275
00:11:12.838 --> 00:11:15.423
Mm. mm. mm...

276
00:11:15.424 --> 00:11:19.427
Um. but sometime...

277
00:11:21.764 --> 00:11:23.473
Sister Grace...

278
00:11:23.474 --> 00:11:25.767
this is one of my residents.
Dr. Mohan.

279
00:11:25.768 --> 00:11:27.519
- Nice to meet you.
- You as well.

280
00:11:27.520 --> 00:11:29.813
I wish we could recruit
as dedicated

281
00:11:29.814 --> 00:11:31.940
and talented young women
as you two.

282
00:11:31.941 --> 00:11:34.651
I imagine it's a calling.
much like medicine.

283
00:11:34.652 --> 00:11:37.237
Yes. very much so.

284
00:11:37.238 --> 00:11:40.365
Sister Grace.
under the microscope.

285
00:11:40.366 --> 00:11:43.910
we're seeing something called
a gram-negative bacteria.

286
00:11:43.911 --> 00:11:45.620
Is that serious?

287
00:11:45.621 --> 00:11:47.789
It can be if left untreated.

288
00:11:47.790 --> 00:11:50.291
But. fortunately. we can give
you a shot of antibiotics.

289
00:11:50.292 --> 00:11:51.960
irrigate your eye
with a liter of saline.

290
00:11:51.961 --> 00:11:54.504
and give you drops to use
at home every few hours.

291
00:11:54.505 --> 00:11:56.298
How did I get it?

292
00:11:58.050 --> 00:12:01.302
So the--the appearance
of the bacteria in your eye

293
00:12:01.303 --> 00:12:03.263
suggests that it's--

294
00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:04.973
it's gonorrhea.

295
00:12:04.974 --> 00:12:06.850
Um. traditionally.
that's a sexually--

296
00:12:06.851 --> 00:12:08.977
I know what gonorrhea is.
Dr. Javadi.

297
00:12:08.978 --> 00:12:11.354
I'm a nun. not a numbskull.

298
00:12:11.355 --> 00:12:14.691
I do a lot of work
at an unhoused shelter.

299
00:12:14.692 --> 00:12:17.402
Are--are you handling
dirty sheets.

300
00:12:17.403 --> 00:12:20.864
pillowcases. soiled clothes?
- Yes.

301
00:12:20.865 --> 00:12:25.076
Uh. part of my day is spent
doing laundry. making beds.

302
00:12:25.077 --> 00:12:27.203
disposing of old clothes.

303
00:12:27.204 --> 00:12:29.080
Do you wear gloves?

304
00:12:29.081 --> 00:12:31.374
- When they're available.
- Okay.

305
00:12:31.375 --> 00:12:33.835
Uh. well. let's--
let's get you your shot

306
00:12:33.836 --> 00:12:35.920
and set up
for irrigating your eye.

307
00:12:35.921 --> 00:12:38.089
I bet we can scrounge up
a couple boxes of gloves

308
00:12:38.090 --> 00:12:39.507
while you're here.

309
00:12:39.508 --> 00:12:42.051
It's important
to protect yourself.

310
00:12:42.052 --> 00:12:43.721
We'll be back.

311
00:12:45.681 --> 00:12:47.807
Why am I here?

312
00:12:47.808 --> 00:12:49.768
I'm not sick.

313
00:12:49.769 --> 00:12:53.521
Oh. we took care of your
husband. Ethan. earlier today.

314
00:12:53.522 --> 00:12:56.524
Is Ethan sick?

315
00:12:56.525 --> 00:12:59.194
Well. he was very ill.

316
00:12:59.195 --> 00:13:02.530
And. um. we did everything
we could to treat him.

317
00:13:02.531 --> 00:13:05.408
but his heart stopped beating.

318
00:13:05.409 --> 00:13:06.701
And...

319
00:13:06.702 --> 00:13:09.079
I'm so sorry to say
that he died.

320
00:13:11.123 --> 00:13:13.583
He died?

321
00:13:13.584 --> 00:13:15.210
Ethan?

322
00:13:15.211 --> 00:13:18.463
No. no.

323
00:13:18.464 --> 00:13:20.382
Are you sure?

324
00:13:22.468 --> 00:13:24.427
Yes.

325
00:13:24.428 --> 00:13:27.222
No. no. no. no. no.

326
00:13:27.223 --> 00:13:29.557
Ethan isn't sick.

327
00:13:29.558 --> 00:13:31.059
No!

328
00:13:31.060 --> 00:13:33.895
I-I know how difficult
this must be for you.

329
00:13:40.319 --> 00:13:42.445
Uh. kidneys look good
on ultrasound.

330
00:13:42.446 --> 00:13:44.197
No intra-abdominal injury.

331
00:13:44.198 --> 00:13:46.157
- Hey. Dylan.
- Robby.

332
00:13:46.158 --> 00:13:48.117
Is this the "tumble down
the stairs" kid--Kylie?

333
00:13:48.118 --> 00:13:49.661
- Yeah.
- And?

334
00:13:49.662 --> 00:13:51.538
I'd like to talk
to the girlfriend first.

335
00:13:51.539 --> 00:13:53.456
away from the little girl.
- We can arrange that.

336
00:13:53.457 --> 00:13:55.166
- Okay.
- Keep us informed.

337
00:13:55.167 --> 00:13:57.752
Yes. keep us informed.

338
00:13:57.753 --> 00:14:01.548
More labs are back
on our abandoned baby Jane Doe.

339
00:14:01.549 --> 00:14:03.758
Everything looks normal so far.

340
00:14:03.759 --> 00:14:06.928
but you seemed
really concerned earlier.

341
00:14:06.929 --> 00:14:08.763
She still needs
a cathed urine.

342
00:14:08.764 --> 00:14:10.224
Or not.

343
00:14:11.642 --> 00:14:13.852
You can't trust
a bagged urine.

344
00:14:13.853 --> 00:14:16.187
Agreed. but we can avoid
the trauma of a catheter.

345
00:14:16.188 --> 00:14:18.147
With a suprapubic tap?

346
00:14:18.148 --> 00:14:21.026
Oh. I may have a trick or two
up my sleeve. Dr. Al-Hashimi.

347
00:14:24.113 --> 00:14:26.614
Hey. Princess. hold up.

348
00:14:26.615 --> 00:14:27.991
Hi.

349
00:14:27.992 --> 00:14:30.201
How you feeling. Mr. Williams?
- Okay.

350
00:14:30.202 --> 00:14:32.453
A little nervous
about going in the machine.

351
00:14:32.454 --> 00:14:34.622
I can get a tad claustrophobic.

352
00:14:34.623 --> 00:14:36.207
Yeah. well. um...

353
00:14:36.208 --> 00:14:38.543
we're sending you for a CT.
not an MRI.

354
00:14:38.544 --> 00:14:41.004
So it's like a open doughnut.

355
00:14:41.005 --> 00:14:42.714
Oh. good.
I like doughnuts.

356
00:14:44.466 --> 00:14:47.093
There you are.
Thought you forgot about me.

357
00:14:47.094 --> 00:14:50.680
Oh. no.
I was just with other patients.

358
00:14:50.681 --> 00:14:53.683
So what do you do for fun?

359
00:14:53.684 --> 00:14:55.560
I mainly do
what my sister likes.

360
00:14:55.561 --> 00:14:57.729
Um. she loves Kennywood
and the zoo.

361
00:14:57.730 --> 00:15:00.356
No. what about you?

362
00:15:00.357 --> 00:15:02.401
What do you like to do?

363
00:15:05.571 --> 00:15:09.741
Um. I used to like. um.
the Renaissance fair.

364
00:15:09.742 --> 00:15:11.743
- Really?
- Yeah.

365
00:15:11.744 --> 00:15:13.745
Isn't that kind of dorky.
though. where everybody

366
00:15:13.746 --> 00:15:15.204
dresses up like
somebody they're not?

367
00:15:15.205 --> 00:15:16.664
Yeah. but that's
the fun. you know?

368
00:15:16.665 --> 00:15:18.499
You can be anyone
or anything you want.

369
00:15:18.500 --> 00:15:20.877
I. um. actually had
this alter ego

370
00:15:20.878 --> 00:15:22.503
that was
a 17th-century French woman--

371
00:15:22.504 --> 00:15:24.714
Stop!

372
00:15:27.843 --> 00:15:29.761
You okay. kid?

373
00:15:29.762 --> 00:15:32.680
That was a doozy.

374
00:15:32.681 --> 00:15:34.766
Okay. are we ready?

375
00:15:34.767 --> 00:15:36.392
Cleaned and dried
with sterile gauze.

376
00:15:36.393 --> 00:15:38.353
- Is that water cold?
- Right out the fridge.

377
00:15:38.354 --> 00:15:40.063
Okay. Jesse.
you can take the armpits.

378
00:15:40.064 --> 00:15:42.065
I'm gonna take the legs.

379
00:15:42.066 --> 00:15:43.650
One. two. three. up.

380
00:15:43.651 --> 00:15:45.860
Dr. Al-Hashimi.
you're gonna be our catcher.

381
00:15:45.861 --> 00:15:48.529
And. Samira. you're gonna do
suprapubic circles

382
00:15:48.530 --> 00:15:50.031
with that gauze.

383
00:15:50.032 --> 00:15:52.659
And the cold
should stimulate voiding.

384
00:15:52.660 --> 00:15:54.911
Even if she pees. it's likely
to be contaminated.

385
00:15:54.912 --> 00:15:56.829
Not according to
the "British Medical Journal."

386
00:15:56.830 --> 00:15:58.414
They did the wee-search.

387
00:15:58.415 --> 00:16:01.334
Any leuks or nitrates.
and we cath.

388
00:16:01.335 --> 00:16:04.504
Oh. Oh.
Dr. Al-Hashimi. get it.

389
00:16:04.505 --> 00:16:06.673
I was gonna invite you
to join the softball team.

390
00:16:06.674 --> 00:16:08.883
but now I'm not so sure.

391
00:16:08.884 --> 00:16:10.343
There we go.

392
00:16:10.344 --> 00:16:12.345
Looks like you got
a good midstream sample.

393
00:16:12.346 --> 00:16:13.888
Here's a fresh blanket.

394
00:16:13.889 --> 00:16:16.140
Okay. Plan.

395
00:16:16.141 --> 00:16:19.560
Ceftriaxone. two-day admit
till blood culture is negative.

396
00:16:19.561 --> 00:16:20.770
Next steps?

397
00:16:20.771 --> 00:16:22.146
Foster care.

398
00:16:22.147 --> 00:16:23.731
Oh. yeah.

399
00:16:23.732 --> 00:16:25.316
Ha.

400
00:16:25.317 --> 00:16:28.111
Someone must have been
in a bad way

401
00:16:28.112 --> 00:16:30.738
to walk away from you.
little one.

402
00:16:30.739 --> 00:16:33.324
We need to call the police?

403
00:16:33.325 --> 00:16:35.744
Let me know
what the urine dip shows.

404
00:16:38.330 --> 00:16:42.500
We will let you know
what the urine dip shows.

405
00:16:42.501 --> 00:16:45.253
You must be Dr. Al-Hashimi.

406
00:16:45.254 --> 00:16:47.088
And you must be Dr. Langdon.

407
00:16:47.089 --> 00:16:49.048
I've heard all about you.

408
00:16:49.049 --> 00:16:50.550
Welcome back.

409
00:16:50.551 --> 00:16:53.261
And this is?
- Uh. Linda Stevens.

410
00:16:53.262 --> 00:16:56.097
One episode of substernal chest
pressure resolved with rest.

411
00:16:56.098 --> 00:16:57.932
12-lead negative for STEMI.

412
00:16:57.933 --> 00:17:00.393
Heading for North 4.

413
00:17:00.394 --> 00:17:03.271
Hello. I'm Dr. Al-Hashimi.

414
00:17:03.272 --> 00:17:05.940
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

415
00:17:05.941 --> 00:17:08.026
Ma'am. this is
a teaching hospital.

416
00:17:08.027 --> 00:17:10.361
Is it okay if some
of our trainees join me?

417
00:17:10.362 --> 00:17:12.405
Not--not a problem.

418
00:17:12.406 --> 00:17:16.367
Dr. Whitaker. Javadi.
Ogilvie. Joy...

419
00:17:16.368 --> 00:17:18.619
gather round.

420
00:17:18.620 --> 00:17:21.164
Dr. Langdon. you are more
than welcome to stay. too.

421
00:17:21.165 --> 00:17:24.000
Uh. maybe for a minute.
We're pretty busy in triage.

422
00:17:24.001 --> 00:17:25.626
Okay.

423
00:17:25.627 --> 00:17:27.962
Ms. Stevens...

424
00:17:27.963 --> 00:17:29.630
I have an app on my phone

425
00:17:29.631 --> 00:17:31.632
that can listen
to our conversation

426
00:17:31.633 --> 00:17:33.676
and the details
of my physical exam

427
00:17:33.677 --> 00:17:35.887
and write it all up
in your medical record.

428
00:17:35.888 --> 00:17:37.805
Wow.

429
00:17:37.806 --> 00:17:41.517
It's protected. confidential.
doesn't even stay on my phone.

430
00:17:41.518 --> 00:17:43.478
And it means I can--
- What's going on?

431
00:17:43.479 --> 00:17:45.646
Some A-hole perp took off
when he saw the cops.

432
00:17:45.647 --> 00:17:47.398
knocked her backwards
off a stool.

433
00:17:47.399 --> 00:17:49.609
- Oh. Jesus.
- Head trauma. no LOC.

434
00:17:49.610 --> 00:17:51.611
Okay. you need
to get checked out.

435
00:17:51.612 --> 00:17:53.780
- I'm fine.
- No choice. It's work-related.

436
00:17:53.781 --> 00:17:55.615
Let's. uh--
let's find her a room

437
00:17:55.616 --> 00:17:58.409
and prep for a burr hole.
- What?

438
00:17:58.410 --> 00:18:00.411
Oh...

439
00:18:00.412 --> 00:18:04.082
I forgot how much you
like to joke. Captain Scurvy.

440
00:18:04.083 --> 00:18:06.501
Who the hell's
Captain Scurvy?

441
00:18:06.502 --> 00:18:08.544
It's an inside thing.

442
00:18:08.545 --> 00:18:11.798
- How's our shoulder guy?
- Oh. he slept like a baby.

443
00:18:11.799 --> 00:18:14.634
CT angio shows
no vascular injury.

444
00:18:14.635 --> 00:18:18.221
What about your slip-and-fall
guy with a labile affect?

445
00:18:18.222 --> 00:18:20.223
Mm. Michael Williams.

446
00:18:20.224 --> 00:18:22.100
He's still in the scanner.

447
00:18:22.101 --> 00:18:24.352
He seems to have settled down.
so he doesn't need babysitting.

448
00:18:24.353 --> 00:18:25.937
Good.
Maybe he's coming around.

449
00:18:25.938 --> 00:18:28.022
Ortho can take Mr. Billings
here up for surgery.

450
00:18:28.023 --> 00:18:29.440
Belay that order. sailor.

451
00:18:29.441 --> 00:18:32.026
Dr. Robinavitch.
- Nurse Hastings.

452
00:18:32.027 --> 00:18:33.694
You can call me Robby.

453
00:18:33.695 --> 00:18:35.447
You can call me Noelle.

454
00:18:37.866 --> 00:18:41.035
Uh. you could just tell me
what the hell's going on here.

455
00:18:41.036 --> 00:18:43.037
This is Noelle.
She's our. um...

456
00:18:43.038 --> 00:18:44.747
Bed control manager.
No. we met.

457
00:18:44.748 --> 00:18:46.040
both:
Case manager.

458
00:18:46.041 --> 00:18:47.625
And this guy
won't be staying.

459
00:18:47.626 --> 00:18:49.544
Oh. he needs surgery.

460
00:18:49.545 --> 00:18:52.338
Which his insurance will pay
for at Westbridge Memorial.

461
00:18:52.339 --> 00:18:54.090
not here.

462
00:18:54.091 --> 00:18:57.718
- Wait. so we have to transfer?
- If--if he's stable.

463
00:18:57.719 --> 00:18:59.428
I believe that he is.

464
00:18:59.429 --> 00:19:00.972
Look on the bright side.

465
00:19:00.973 --> 00:19:03.141
We're gonna free up a bed.
discharge a patient.

466
00:19:03.142 --> 00:19:05.685
I mean. that's great for us.
not so good for him.

467
00:19:05.686 --> 00:19:07.937
He will get great care
at Westbridge.

468
00:19:07.938 --> 00:19:10.523
Don't you agree. Robby?

469
00:19:10.524 --> 00:19:13.359
- I'm sure that he will.
- Yeah.

470
00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:15.278
What am I missing?

471
00:19:15.279 --> 00:19:17.488
Is there something else
happening with Allen Billings

472
00:19:17.489 --> 00:19:19.198
that I don't know about?

473
00:19:19.199 --> 00:19:20.658
Not medically.

474
00:19:20.659 --> 00:19:24.078
This is just
a simple insurance transfer.

475
00:19:24.079 --> 00:19:26.206
Mm. yeah. okay.

476
00:19:30.419 --> 00:19:32.753
What's that about?

477
00:19:32.754 --> 00:19:35.756
- Nothing.
- Didn't feel like nothing.

478
00:19:35.757 --> 00:19:38.092
Dr. McKay has a very
heightened sense of empathy.

479
00:19:38.093 --> 00:19:39.594
Meaning?

480
00:19:39.595 --> 00:19:41.929
Meaning she's good
at picking up on stuff.

481
00:19:41.930 --> 00:19:43.931
You didn't say
anything. did you?

482
00:19:43.932 --> 00:19:45.266
Nope.

483
00:19:45.267 --> 00:19:47.310
I subscribe
to the Falstaff advice.

484
00:19:47.311 --> 00:19:49.103
Discretion
is the better part of valor.

485
00:19:49.104 --> 00:19:50.479
Oh.

486
00:19:50.480 --> 00:19:52.315
You still planning
on leaving tonight?

487
00:19:52.316 --> 00:19:54.233
Yep.

488
00:19:54.234 --> 00:19:58.112
I don't understand why
you can't leave in the morning.

489
00:19:58.113 --> 00:19:59.822
Will you excuse me
for a second?

490
00:19:59.823 --> 00:20:01.657
I got to go talk to a patient
while she's separated

491
00:20:01.658 --> 00:20:02.992
from her caregiver.
- Oh. yeah.

492
00:20:02.993 --> 00:20:04.744
That doesn't sound ideal.
- It's not ideal.

493
00:20:04.745 --> 00:20:06.746
I got to figure out
what's going on.

494
00:20:06.747 --> 00:20:08.915
And I'll find you
before I leave.

495
00:20:08.916 --> 00:20:10.375
Okay.

496
00:20:13.045 --> 00:20:16.589
Okay. you got to stop this.

497
00:20:16.590 --> 00:20:18.674
Hastings.

498
00:20:18.675 --> 00:20:20.051
Evans.

499
00:20:20.052 --> 00:20:21.969
Hope you know
what you're doing.

500
00:20:21.970 --> 00:20:24.972
What is that supposed to mean?

501
00:20:24.973 --> 00:20:27.475
I'm a big girl.

502
00:20:27.476 --> 00:20:30.645
Okay. big girl.

503
00:20:30.646 --> 00:20:31.979
I'm fine.

504
00:20:31.980 --> 00:20:33.941
That's good.
Follow my finger.

505
00:20:35.567 --> 00:20:37.068
How's the head?

506
00:20:37.069 --> 00:20:38.986
It's a little sore.

507
00:20:38.987 --> 00:20:41.864
Lean forward.
Let me take a look.

508
00:20:41.865 --> 00:20:44.909
Yeah. you're gonna have
a pretty good goose egg.

509
00:20:44.910 --> 00:20:47.370
Headache?
- A little.

510
00:20:47.371 --> 00:20:48.996
I can get you some Tylenol.

511
00:20:48.997 --> 00:20:50.665
unless you need
something stronger.

512
00:20:50.666 --> 00:20:53.376
Oh. no. that's okay.
I'm not very drug tolerant.

513
00:20:53.377 --> 00:20:55.295
Lucky you.

514
00:20:57.798 --> 00:20:59.799
You know.
I'm glad you're back.

515
00:20:59.800 --> 00:21:04.095
Thanks.
Yeah. I'm glad to be back.

516
00:21:04.096 --> 00:21:06.389
You know why I was away?
- I should see my patient--

517
00:21:06.390 --> 00:21:09.016
Um. no. not really.

518
00:21:09.017 --> 00:21:10.685
I mean. I heard rumors.
but I learned

519
00:21:10.686 --> 00:21:12.144
a long time ago not to listen.

520
00:21:12.145 --> 00:21:13.521
- I was in rehab...
- Oh.

521
00:21:13.522 --> 00:21:15.564
For an addiction to benzos.

522
00:21:15.565 --> 00:21:17.525
Oh.

523
00:21:17.526 --> 00:21:20.194
Yeah. but I'm--I'm clean now.

524
00:21:20.195 --> 00:21:21.988
A-and it never affected
my work.

525
00:21:21.989 --> 00:21:23.614
I just...

526
00:21:23.615 --> 00:21:26.326
needed to get it all out
of my system once and for all.

527
00:21:28.578 --> 00:21:31.872
Yeah. I-I didn't handle things
the way I should have.

528
00:21:31.873 --> 00:21:36.711
I thought I could treat myself.
and I let a lot of people down.

529
00:21:36.712 --> 00:21:39.422
I'm sorry. Mel.

530
00:21:39.423 --> 00:21:42.425
You never let me down.

531
00:21:42.426 --> 00:21:43.634
Yeah.

532
00:21:43.635 --> 00:21:45.428
Yeah. I did.

533
00:21:45.429 --> 00:21:48.431
I should be setting an example.
not a cautionary tale.

534
00:21:50.225 --> 00:21:51.976
Hey.

535
00:21:51.977 --> 00:21:54.228
How you doing?
- I'm okay.

536
00:21:54.229 --> 00:21:56.981
Listen. I'm really sorry
about all that.

537
00:21:56.982 --> 00:21:58.941
The guy robbed
a liquor store last night.

538
00:21:58.942 --> 00:22:01.027
He tried to get away
on a bicycle

539
00:22:01.028 --> 00:22:02.737
but wiped out
and took off on foot.

540
00:22:02.738 --> 00:22:04.322
He must've hobbled in here--

541
00:22:04.323 --> 00:22:06.657
more so to hide out than
to get stitched up. I think.

542
00:22:06.658 --> 00:22:08.367
- You catch him?
- We will.

543
00:22:08.368 --> 00:22:10.244
Anything you could tell us
about him will help.

544
00:22:10.245 --> 00:22:12.204
You think he gave
legit information?

545
00:22:12.205 --> 00:22:15.708
Probably not. but it's
all we have at the moment.

546
00:22:15.709 --> 00:22:17.376
If we do find him.

547
00:22:17.377 --> 00:22:20.421
you may have to testify
in court. Dr. King.

548
00:22:20.422 --> 00:22:22.757
- "In court"?
- As a material witness.

549
00:22:22.758 --> 00:22:25.676
Attest to his injuries.
his treatments--

550
00:22:25.677 --> 00:22:27.178
simple stuff.

551
00:22:27.179 --> 00:22:28.929
Yeah. but we'll cross
that bridge

552
00:22:28.930 --> 00:22:30.765
when we come to it. right?

553
00:22:30.766 --> 00:22:32.850
Mel?

554
00:22:32.851 --> 00:22:34.935
Rest here a minute.
I'll be right back.

555
00:22:34.936 --> 00:22:36.104
Mm.

556
00:22:38.440 --> 00:22:40.691
You know. I'm--
I'm fine. really. I should--

557
00:22:40.692 --> 00:22:43.111
Ten minutes. please.
Doctor's orders.

558
00:22:45.614 --> 00:22:48.325
ER can be a little bright
and noisy.

559
00:22:52.996 --> 00:22:55.122
Dorsalis pedis

560
00:22:55.123 --> 00:22:58.667
and posterior tibial pulses
2 plus and equal.

561
00:22:58.668 --> 00:23:00.336
Your exam is perfect. ma'am.

562
00:23:00.337 --> 00:23:02.421
Oh. that is good to hear.

563
00:23:02.422 --> 00:23:04.965
I will be back when
your blood tests are ready.

564
00:23:04.966 --> 00:23:07.051
Let us know
if the chest pain returns.

565
00:23:07.052 --> 00:23:09.512
- Thank you.
- You are so welcome.

566
00:23:11.348 --> 00:23:12.765
What do you think?

567
00:23:12.766 --> 00:23:14.350
Well. I don't think
it's cardiac.

568
00:23:14.351 --> 00:23:16.143
I mean. what do you think
of the app?

569
00:23:16.144 --> 00:23:18.729
I mean. it's hard to say
without seeing the full thing.

570
00:23:18.730 --> 00:23:21.273
Take a look.

571
00:23:21.274 --> 00:23:22.733
Oh. my God.

572
00:23:22.734 --> 00:23:24.693
Do you know how much time
this will save?

573
00:23:24.694 --> 00:23:27.988
Studies show you can spend
80% less time charting.

574
00:23:27.989 --> 00:23:29.740
You'll get out of here sooner.

575
00:23:29.741 --> 00:23:31.992
improving both patient
and physician satisfaction.

576
00:23:31.993 --> 00:23:33.577
Oh. excuse me.

577
00:23:33.578 --> 00:23:35.996
It says here she takes
Risperdal. an antipsychotic.

578
00:23:35.997 --> 00:23:38.374
She takes Restoril
when needed for sleep.

579
00:23:38.375 --> 00:23:39.750
So is that. um...

580
00:23:39.751 --> 00:23:42.211
AI. "almost intelligent."

581
00:23:42.212 --> 00:23:45.923
Generative AI is
98% accurate at present.

582
00:23:45.924 --> 00:23:47.758
You must always
carefully proofread

583
00:23:47.759 --> 00:23:49.343
and correct the minor errors.

584
00:23:49.344 --> 00:23:50.928
It's excellent but not perfect.

585
00:23:50.929 --> 00:23:53.347
This is amazing.

586
00:23:53.348 --> 00:23:55.015
<i>Moteshakeram.</i>

587
00:23:55.016 --> 00:23:57.768
<i>Khahesh mikonam.</i>

588
00:23:57.769 --> 00:24:00.729
You speak Farsi?
- I did my undergrad at UCLA.

589
00:24:00.730 --> 00:24:02.565
A lot of my friends
were Persian.

590
00:24:02.566 --> 00:24:04.275
So you learned the language?

591
00:24:04.276 --> 00:24:06.235
Enough to break the ice.

592
00:24:06.236 --> 00:24:08.405
I am impressed.

593
00:24:09.614 --> 00:24:11.157
Me too...

594
00:24:11.158 --> 00:24:12.741
that you had friends.

595
00:24:12.742 --> 00:24:15.035
Dr. Whitaker.
I said hello to your widow

596
00:24:15.036 --> 00:24:17.121
with Alzheimer's. but she only
wants to talk to a doctor.

597
00:24:17.122 --> 00:24:19.373
She's also very overdue
for a diaper change.

598
00:24:19.374 --> 00:24:21.375
Okay. Yeah. thank you.

599
00:24:21.376 --> 00:24:23.420
Uh. Ogilvie. you're with me.

600
00:24:24.796 --> 00:24:26.005
Come on.

601
00:24:26.006 --> 00:24:28.717
Ah. Mrs. Bostick?

602
00:24:30.844 --> 00:24:32.136
Takotsubo?

603
00:24:32.137 --> 00:24:33.387
Broken heart syndrome?
- Uh. no.

604
00:24:33.388 --> 00:24:34.430
Aah!

605
00:24:34.431 --> 00:24:35.890
Hello?

606
00:24:35.891 --> 00:24:37.391
Hey.

607
00:24:37.392 --> 00:24:39.226
Um. you wanted to see me?

608
00:24:39.227 --> 00:24:40.978
No.

609
00:24:40.979 --> 00:24:43.147
Who are you?

610
00:24:43.148 --> 00:24:44.940
I'm Dr. Whitaker.

611
00:24:44.941 --> 00:24:47.067
We talked about your husband?

612
00:24:47.068 --> 00:24:49.904
Oh. Ethan.

613
00:24:49.905 --> 00:24:52.781
Oh. can he please come see me?

614
00:24:52.782 --> 00:24:55.117
Um...

615
00:24:55.118 --> 00:24:57.578
um...

616
00:24:57.579 --> 00:24:59.497
no.

617
00:24:59.498 --> 00:25:03.083
Unfortunately.
he was very sick...

618
00:25:03.084 --> 00:25:05.462
and he died.

619
00:25:07.672 --> 00:25:09.632
Ethan?

620
00:25:09.633 --> 00:25:11.842
Died?

621
00:25:11.843 --> 00:25:13.260
{\an8}No.

622
00:25:13.261 --> 00:25:14.595
{\an8}Oh. no.

623
00:25:14.596 --> 00:25:17.223
{\an8}No. that's impossible.

624
00:25:17.224 --> 00:25:20.226
{\an8}No.

625
00:25:20.227 --> 00:25:23.270
{\an8}No. no. no. no. no.

626
00:25:23.271 --> 00:25:25.439
What do you like
to do for fun?

627
00:25:25.440 --> 00:25:26.857
I love horseback riding.

628
00:25:26.858 --> 00:25:28.901
- Does your dad take you?
- Yep.

629
00:25:28.902 --> 00:25:30.486
Sometimes he even rides.

630
00:25:30.487 --> 00:25:32.738
but most of the time.
he just watches me.

631
00:25:32.739 --> 00:25:35.449
Have you ever fallen off?
Have you ever been thrown?

632
00:25:35.450 --> 00:25:38.452
Nope.
I'm a very good rider.

633
00:25:38.453 --> 00:25:40.788
- Do you have your own horse?
- I wish.

634
00:25:40.789 --> 00:25:42.998
We live in an apartment.

635
00:25:42.999 --> 00:25:45.668
Okay. Kylie. we need
to take some blood now.

636
00:25:45.669 --> 00:25:47.378
Do you have to do that?

637
00:25:47.379 --> 00:25:50.297
Yeah. but I promise
it'll go super fast

638
00:25:50.298 --> 00:25:52.841
and only hurt
for. like. a moment. okay?

639
00:25:52.842 --> 00:25:56.470
So I'm just gonna
put this rubber band

640
00:25:56.471 --> 00:25:59.473
around your arm to help me
find your vein better.

641
00:25:59.474 --> 00:26:03.644
And then this makes sure
no germs get in your body

642
00:26:03.645 --> 00:26:05.521
when we do it.

643
00:26:05.522 --> 00:26:08.482
Okay. now you're just gonna
feel this teeny little prick.

644
00:26:08.483 --> 00:26:10.527
But you can look away. okay?

645
00:26:12.612 --> 00:26:14.739
Worst part's over.

646
00:26:16.866 --> 00:26:18.784
Tough little girl.

647
00:26:18.785 --> 00:26:20.369
Yeah. well.
little girls can be

648
00:26:20.370 --> 00:26:22.705
just as tough as little boys.
even tougher.

649
00:26:22.706 --> 00:26:25.291
Yes. I just hope it's not
because she's become

650
00:26:25.292 --> 00:26:26.959
accustomed to pain.

651
00:26:26.960 --> 00:26:29.295
At the very least.
she's gonna need a visual exam

652
00:26:29.296 --> 00:26:31.422
of external genitalia
to look for signs of trauma.

653
00:26:31.423 --> 00:26:33.299
I can have Dr. Al-Hashimi--

654
00:26:33.300 --> 00:26:35.343
No. she's my patient.
I can do it.

655
00:26:43.768 --> 00:26:45.853
Nice and clear.

656
00:26:45.854 --> 00:26:50.524
Uh. with an infection.
it'd be kind of cloudy.

657
00:26:50.525 --> 00:26:52.526
Joy. get ready to spike
the third bottle here

658
00:26:52.527 --> 00:26:53.902
after I clamp.

659
00:26:53.903 --> 00:26:55.738
- All good in here?
- Yes.

660
00:26:55.739 --> 00:26:58.532
Uh. Dr. Whitaker was just
explaining that with SBP.

661
00:26:58.533 --> 00:27:00.743
we would see
a turbid appearance.

662
00:27:00.744 --> 00:27:03.579
However. he failed to mention
that bloody fluid indicates

663
00:27:03.580 --> 00:27:05.623
either a traumatic tap
or the likelihood

664
00:27:05.624 --> 00:27:07.207
of hepatocellular carcinoma.

665
00:27:07.208 --> 00:27:09.752
in which case.
we would send for cytology.

666
00:27:09.753 --> 00:27:11.003
That is correct.

667
00:27:11.004 --> 00:27:12.838
Kid knows his shit.

668
00:27:12.839 --> 00:27:15.467
He's so smart.

669
00:27:18.553 --> 00:27:20.846
- Oh. hey.
- Hey.

670
00:27:20.847 --> 00:27:22.890
How's it feel
to officially be a doctor?

671
00:27:22.891 --> 00:27:25.017
It's pretty cool. actually.

672
00:27:25.018 --> 00:27:26.810
Uh. I get
my first paycheck today.

673
00:27:26.811 --> 00:27:29.772
It's only for the first week.
but I will take it.

674
00:27:29.773 --> 00:27:33.609
- How are the med students?
- Um. Joy is pretty peculiar.

675
00:27:33.610 --> 00:27:36.570
And the other guy. Ogilvie.
is really smart

676
00:27:36.571 --> 00:27:38.781
and likes to show people.

677
00:27:38.782 --> 00:27:41.283
- He's obnoxious.
- Well...

678
00:27:41.284 --> 00:27:43.786
What he is.
is your competition.

679
00:27:43.787 --> 00:27:46.831
He's a gunner.
- Yeah. right.

680
00:27:49.584 --> 00:27:51.835
He's not my competition.

681
00:27:51.836 --> 00:27:54.922
He's from out of state
for a four-week sub-internship.

682
00:27:54.923 --> 00:27:57.591
You don't think he's angling
for an emergency residency spot

683
00:27:57.592 --> 00:27:59.426
here next year?

684
00:27:59.427 --> 00:28:02.596
- I mean. even if he was...
- What?

685
00:28:02.597 --> 00:28:06.518
He couldn't possibly compete
with your gigantic brain?

686
00:28:10.105 --> 00:28:13.066
I'd step it up
if I were you. Crash.

687
00:28:15.402 --> 00:28:18.320
Oh. she's still calling
you that. huh?

688
00:28:18.321 --> 00:28:20.114
I don't really
even care anymore.

689
00:28:20.115 --> 00:28:22.032
I mean. she still calls you
Huckleberry.

690
00:28:22.033 --> 00:28:25.035
Yeah. but. you know.
friends now. so...

691
00:28:25.036 --> 00:28:28.038
Friends don't give each other
shitty nicknames.

692
00:28:28.039 --> 00:28:31.126
You think Huckleberry
is a shitty nickname?

693
00:28:32.585 --> 00:28:33.836
No.

694
00:28:33.837 --> 00:28:35.838
No. H-Huckleberry is cute.

695
00:28:35.839 --> 00:28:37.172
Oh.

696
00:28:37.173 --> 00:28:39.842
It's cool.
It's not like Crash.

697
00:28:39.843 --> 00:28:42.052
Oh. come on. man.
Crash is pretty cool.

698
00:28:42.053 --> 00:28:44.304
It's. like. you know...
Crash.

699
00:28:44.305 --> 00:28:46.974
It's got momentum.

700
00:28:46.975 --> 00:28:49.560
Dr. Javadi. Dr. Whitaker.

701
00:28:49.561 --> 00:28:51.478
Oh. I'm--I'm still
a student doctor.

702
00:28:51.479 --> 00:28:53.313
Whitaker's the real deal now.

703
00:28:53.314 --> 00:28:55.315
Right.

704
00:28:55.316 --> 00:28:56.984
Welcome back.

705
00:28:56.985 --> 00:28:59.069
Thanks.
Yeah. thank you.

706
00:28:59.070 --> 00:29:01.072
It's good to be back.

707
00:29:02.866 --> 00:29:06.994
Okay. I will be in exile
on Triage Island

708
00:29:06.995 --> 00:29:08.871
with the rest
of the drug addicts.

709
00:29:08.872 --> 00:29:11.206
if anyone needs me.

710
00:29:11.207 --> 00:29:13.667
- That was weird.
- Very.

711
00:29:16.504 --> 00:29:17.547
{\an8}What?

712
00:29:36.107 --> 00:29:37.817
{\an8}Mm-hmm.

713
00:29:39.611 --> 00:29:41.987
Ooh!
That's got to hurt.

714
00:29:41.988 --> 00:29:44.531
Dr. Langdon. Clint Hansen.
his cousin Mona.

715
00:29:44.532 --> 00:29:45.741
How'd this happen?

716
00:29:47.118 --> 00:29:49.244
Bacon grease
from a big griddle.

717
00:29:49.245 --> 00:29:50.913
Oh. looks like
more than a splatter.

718
00:29:50.914 --> 00:29:52.706
Yeah. some fool poured it
in the sink

719
00:29:52.707 --> 00:29:54.374
while I was washing dishes.
- I was so far away.

720
00:29:54.375 --> 00:29:55.959
You reached for the soap
without even looking.

721
00:29:55.960 --> 00:29:57.294
You couldn't hear me?

722
00:29:57.295 --> 00:29:58.879
No. not with
the water running.

723
00:29:58.880 --> 00:30:00.714
Who the hell pours
bacon grease down the drain?

724
00:30:00.715 --> 00:30:02.549
There's a jar under the sink.
- You could have told me that.

725
00:30:02.550 --> 00:30:04.218
You're a guest in my house.

726
00:30:04.219 --> 00:30:05.803
and now you've totally
fucked up my plumbing.

727
00:30:05.804 --> 00:30:07.596
Okay. how about we focus
on treating this burn?

728
00:30:07.597 --> 00:30:09.223
I'll grab the LET.

729
00:30:09.224 --> 00:30:10.557
We're gonna need to trim
off some of the dead skin

730
00:30:10.558 --> 00:30:11.892
so it doesn't get infected.

731
00:30:11.893 --> 00:30:13.477
I'm in charge
of the brunch buffet.

732
00:30:13.478 --> 00:30:15.395
Can you make it fast?
- Sure. Yeah. we--

733
00:30:15.396 --> 00:30:17.356
This one came in by car.
All I got is a name.

734
00:30:17.357 --> 00:30:18.941
Orlando Diaz.
- What's the story?

735
00:30:18.942 --> 00:30:20.400
He tripped over some rebar.

736
00:30:20.401 --> 00:30:21.902
- Tripped or fainted?
- I don't know.

737
00:30:21.903 --> 00:30:24.238
Orlando. open your eyes.

738
00:30:24.239 --> 00:30:25.906
Hit his head?
- I guess.

739
00:30:25.907 --> 00:30:27.741
- Why didn't you call 911?
- He wouldn't let me.

740
00:30:27.742 --> 00:30:29.368
He was talking--
not so much now.

741
00:30:29.369 --> 00:30:31.745
Orlando. Mr. Diaz.

742
00:30:31.746 --> 00:30:33.455
Jesus.
- He drunk?

743
00:30:33.456 --> 00:30:34.706
No. Ketones on his breath.

744
00:30:34.707 --> 00:30:36.291
He diabetic?
- I don't know.

745
00:30:36.292 --> 00:30:38.377
Altered head trauma.
possible DKA.

746
00:30:38.378 --> 00:30:39.796
Call it overhead.

747
00:30:41.548 --> 00:30:44.591
<i>Code trauma tier one now.
Code trauma tier one now.</i>

748
00:30:44.592 --> 00:30:47.594
Dr. Whitaker.
your assessment was spot-on.

749
00:30:47.595 --> 00:30:50.097
Your Alzheimer's widow
definitely needs placement.

750
00:30:50.098 --> 00:30:51.974
Do you have a nursing home
that can take her today?

751
00:30:51.975 --> 00:30:53.517
I wish.

752
00:30:53.518 --> 00:30:55.519
Medicare requires
a three-day hospitalization

753
00:30:55.520 --> 00:30:57.020
before they'll approve that.

754
00:30:57.021 --> 00:30:58.981
I don't really have
a reason to admit her.

755
00:30:58.982 --> 00:31:01.775
But I do.
She's gravely disabled.

756
00:31:01.776 --> 00:31:04.111
I'll put her on a cycle.
We'll make it work.

757
00:31:04.112 --> 00:31:06.780
Thank you. Caleb.

758
00:31:06.781 --> 00:31:09.116
Yeah. you have
a few moments. Michael?

759
00:31:09.117 --> 00:31:11.118
Actually. I do not.

760
00:31:11.119 --> 00:31:14.288
But once I get things settled
here. I will come and find you.

761
00:31:14.289 --> 00:31:15.290
Okay.

762
00:31:17.458 --> 00:31:19.334
Dr. Robby. Dylan just
talked to the girlfriend.

763
00:31:19.335 --> 00:31:20.752
Robby!

764
00:31:20.753 --> 00:31:22.671
You'll have
to fill me in in a minute.

765
00:31:22.672 --> 00:31:24.214
What do you got?
- AMS.

766
00:31:24.215 --> 00:31:26.008
I can't tell if he fell
'cause he was altered

767
00:31:26.009 --> 00:31:27.968
or he's altered
because he fell.

768
00:31:27.969 --> 00:31:31.430
There's ketones on his breath.
- Okay. I got this. Thank you.

769
00:31:31.431 --> 00:31:33.223
All right.
I guess it's just us.

770
00:31:33.224 --> 00:31:35.142
Um. what did the girlfriend
have to say?

771
00:31:35.143 --> 00:31:37.436
Well. Gina seems a little
confused and on edge by this.

772
00:31:37.437 --> 00:31:39.271
but I'm not suspicious
about abuse on her part.

773
00:31:39.272 --> 00:31:40.814
What about Kylie's father?

774
00:31:40.815 --> 00:31:42.357
Well. I'm a social worker.
not a mind reader.

775
00:31:42.358 --> 00:31:43.567
I need to speak with him.

776
00:31:43.568 --> 00:31:45.235
Yeah.
he's supposed to come in.

777
00:31:45.236 --> 00:31:47.279
If he doesn't.
looks pretty guilty.

778
00:31:47.280 --> 00:31:49.489
Let's not jump
to any conclusions just yet.

779
00:31:49.490 --> 00:31:50.908
I'm not jumping.

780
00:31:50.909 --> 00:31:54.036
I'm just saying.
if this dude doesn't show up.

781
00:31:54.037 --> 00:31:56.163
hell. I'll go find him myself.

782
00:31:56.164 --> 00:31:58.665
Kidding.

783
00:31:58.666 --> 00:32:01.251
I will speak to Kylie
before her dad gets here.

784
00:32:01.252 --> 00:32:03.170
If he shows up.

785
00:32:03.171 --> 00:32:04.922
Yes.

786
00:32:04.923 --> 00:32:07.507
That's definitely ketones.
We need to do an Accu-Check.

787
00:32:07.508 --> 00:32:09.217
I'm on it.
He's tachy at 124.

788
00:32:09.218 --> 00:32:12.179
Pulse ox 97.
BP's 106/72.

789
00:32:12.180 --> 00:32:14.890
- Lung sliding bilaterally.
- Good bowel sounds.

790
00:32:14.891 --> 00:32:16.558
Abdomen is soft. non-tender.

791
00:32:16.559 --> 00:32:19.019
How do you know
it's non-tender?

792
00:32:19.020 --> 00:32:21.063
Because I didn't see
any grimacing.

793
00:32:21.064 --> 00:32:23.774
He's altered. He didn't even
flinch for the IV start.

794
00:32:23.775 --> 00:32:26.652
- I meant to say non-rigid.
- Huh.

795
00:32:26.653 --> 00:32:28.236
Toes down--going bilaterally.

796
00:32:28.237 --> 00:32:29.738
No evidence of upper
motor neuron deficit.

797
00:32:29.739 --> 00:32:31.114
Good.

798
00:32:31.115 --> 00:32:33.075
- E-FAST negative.
- How can I assist?

799
00:32:33.076 --> 00:32:35.911
You can check in
with Dr. McKay or Dr. Santos.

800
00:32:35.912 --> 00:32:37.579
If you don't mind.
I'd like to observe.

801
00:32:37.580 --> 00:32:39.247
learn how you handle things.

802
00:32:39.248 --> 00:32:41.083
Whoa. blood sugar's
critical high--it's over 500.

803
00:32:41.084 --> 00:32:42.501
Ding. ding. ding. ding.

804
00:32:42.502 --> 00:32:44.294
Sounds like
diabetic ketoacidosis.

805
00:32:44.295 --> 00:32:46.088
We need to start treating that.
then right to CT

806
00:32:46.089 --> 00:32:47.923
to rule out
an intracranial bleed.

807
00:32:47.924 --> 00:32:49.841
Severe respiratory distress
coming in--ETA three minutes.

808
00:32:49.842 --> 00:32:51.301
I'll stick them in Trauma 1.
- Yep.

809
00:32:51.302 --> 00:32:53.095
Would you like me
to take that?

810
00:32:53.096 --> 00:32:54.471
Yes. please. Thank you.

811
00:32:54.472 --> 00:32:56.306
This guy needs
an insulin drip. right?

812
00:32:56.307 --> 00:32:57.724
0.1 units per kilo?

813
00:32:57.725 --> 00:32:59.559
No. not without knowing
his potassium.

814
00:32:59.560 --> 00:33:01.561
Insulin causes
an intracellular shift.

815
00:33:01.562 --> 00:33:03.563
And if the potassium is under
3.5. the drip would kill him.

816
00:33:03.564 --> 00:33:04.940
That is very true.

817
00:33:04.941 --> 00:33:06.733
We can start
with lactated ringers.

818
00:33:06.734 --> 00:33:08.485
1 liter per hour
until we get the results

819
00:33:08.486 --> 00:33:10.237
from the chem-7 and the VBG.

820
00:33:10.238 --> 00:33:11.738
Why is he in DKA?

821
00:33:11.739 --> 00:33:13.115
Maybe he's not taking
enough insulin.

822
00:33:13.116 --> 00:33:14.574
More frequently.
a precipitating event

823
00:33:14.575 --> 00:33:16.076
can be identified.
such as pneumonia.

824
00:33:16.077 --> 00:33:17.619
urinary tract infection.
stroke.

825
00:33:17.620 --> 00:33:19.121
myocardial infarction. pancreatitis.

826
00:33:19.122 --> 00:33:20.956
Yeah. we always
check for those.

827
00:33:20.957 --> 00:33:24.376
They're part of the standard
order set. right. Dr. Mohan?

828
00:33:32.176 --> 00:33:34.136
He's from crazy
Grandpa Jimmy's side.

829
00:33:34.137 --> 00:33:35.929
She's from my grandfather's
brother's side.

830
00:33:35.930 --> 00:33:37.848
Grandpa Ricky
is still a psycho.

831
00:33:37.849 --> 00:33:40.434
Clearly runs in the family.
- Well. hold on.

832
00:33:40.435 --> 00:33:43.562
Your grandparents
are Ricky and Jimmy Hansen...

833
00:33:43.563 --> 00:33:45.230
from the racing family?

834
00:33:45.231 --> 00:33:46.773
Unfortunately.

835
00:33:46.774 --> 00:33:48.900
I got something
that needs attention.

836
00:33:48.901 --> 00:33:50.611
Not another baby.

837
00:33:52.572 --> 00:33:54.407
Sorry. Excuse me.

838
00:33:56.784 --> 00:33:58.660
This is Mr. Randall.

839
00:33:58.661 --> 00:34:01.371
He's been erect
for the last eight hours.

840
00:34:01.372 --> 00:34:03.123
Should have gone down
by now. right?

841
00:34:03.124 --> 00:34:04.541
It happens.

842
00:34:04.542 --> 00:34:06.043
It's a good thing
you came in. Mr. Randall.

843
00:34:06.044 --> 00:34:07.544
I'll take him right back.

844
00:34:07.545 --> 00:34:09.379
Do you mind finishing up
with the Bickersons?

845
00:34:09.380 --> 00:34:10.630
I'd rather not.

846
00:34:10.631 --> 00:34:13.133
- So. Mr. Randall--
- Ian.

847
00:34:13.134 --> 00:34:15.385
Ian. did you take anything

848
00:34:15.386 --> 00:34:17.637
that might have led
to this condition?

849
00:34:17.638 --> 00:34:20.640
I used an ED injection--
two. actually.

850
00:34:20.641 --> 00:34:24.394
I gave myself a second shot.
one on each side.

851
00:34:24.395 --> 00:34:27.606
So double
the recommended dosage?

852
00:34:27.607 --> 00:34:29.399
Uh...

853
00:34:29.400 --> 00:34:31.693
It's our wedding anniversary.

854
00:34:31.694 --> 00:34:33.612
Ah. Is this a big one?

855
00:34:33.613 --> 00:34:36.281
The anniversary.
is it important?

856
00:34:36.282 --> 00:34:38.867
Like. uh. significant?
Like. a milestone or--

857
00:34:38.868 --> 00:34:40.660
- It's our 20th.
- Oh. nice.

858
00:34:40.661 --> 00:34:43.955
Well done.
Congratulations.

859
00:34:43.956 --> 00:34:45.332
Glucose 521.

860
00:34:45.333 --> 00:34:46.708
Sodium 129.

861
00:34:46.709 --> 00:34:48.668
Potassium's 3.7.

862
00:34:48.669 --> 00:34:50.337
Chloride's 97.

863
00:34:50.338 --> 00:34:52.297
Bicarb's 8.
- Meaning?

864
00:34:52.298 --> 00:34:55.509
We can start the insulin drip
and add 20 of K to each liter.

865
00:34:55.510 --> 00:34:57.719
Big anion gap of 24.

866
00:34:57.720 --> 00:34:59.096
It should be under 10.

867
00:34:59.097 --> 00:35:00.847
We follow it
to assess progress.

868
00:35:00.848 --> 00:35:03.517
Actually. the 2024
international guidelines

869
00:35:03.518 --> 00:35:05.435
state that anion gap
should not be used.

870
00:35:05.436 --> 00:35:07.687
as they can be misleading
in the presence

871
00:35:07.688 --> 00:35:10.524
of hyperchloremic
metabolic acidosis.

872
00:35:10.525 --> 00:35:13.026
I-I recently had
a case in the ICU.

873
00:35:13.027 --> 00:35:15.570
VBG is back--
pH of 6.97.

874
00:35:15.571 --> 00:35:16.696
Normal's 7.4.

875
00:35:16.697 --> 00:35:18.281
What causes the acidemia?

876
00:35:18.282 --> 00:35:20.242
Without insulin.
the body can't use glucose.

877
00:35:20.243 --> 00:35:22.244
so it breaks down
fat-producing ketones.

878
00:35:22.245 --> 00:35:24.538
leading to severe acidosis.
which can cause cardiac arrest.

879
00:35:24.539 --> 00:35:26.873
But the hyperglycemia causes
the body to excrete more water

880
00:35:26.874 --> 00:35:29.042
and electrolytes.
leading to severe dehydration.

881
00:35:29.043 --> 00:35:30.919
cardiac and renal dysfunction.

882
00:35:30.920 --> 00:35:32.671
Insulin drip.
fluids with KCL.

883
00:35:32.672 --> 00:35:35.549
capillary glucose every hour.
chem-7 every four hours.

884
00:35:35.550 --> 00:35:37.175
ICU is gonna want
a double lumen midline. too.

885
00:35:37.176 --> 00:35:38.426
both:
I can do it.

886
00:35:38.427 --> 00:35:39.886
- 6 1/2 gloves.
- 7 1/2 gloves.

887
00:35:39.887 --> 00:35:41.263
Can I just say.
we evaluate our students

888
00:35:41.264 --> 00:35:42.889
not only on their fund
of knowledge

889
00:35:42.890 --> 00:35:44.724
and on their
procedural mastery.

890
00:35:44.725 --> 00:35:46.268
but. also.
maybe more importantly.

891
00:35:46.269 --> 00:35:48.186
on their skills
as team players?

892
00:35:48.187 --> 00:35:50.856
- He can do it.
- She--she can do it.

893
00:35:50.857 --> 00:35:52.649
<i>Otero. will you update
everyone?</i>

894
00:35:52.650 --> 00:35:54.985
Barry Mitchell.
Eating breakfast at Pamela's.

895
00:35:54.986 --> 00:35:56.653
Sudden onset
respiratory distress.

896
00:35:56.654 --> 00:35:58.113
Some stridor.

897
00:35:58.114 --> 00:36:00.073
Decent pulse ox
but trouble speaking.

898
00:36:00.074 --> 00:36:02.075
- And they tried the Heimlich?
- Three times.

899
00:36:02.076 --> 00:36:04.745
Any history of asthma?

900
00:36:06.497 --> 00:36:08.456
Set up for intubation.
- Agreed.

901
00:36:08.457 --> 00:36:11.084
Okay. sir. scoot across.

902
00:36:11.085 --> 00:36:13.837
Always a good sign when
they slide over on their own.

903
00:36:13.838 --> 00:36:16.423
Came from a diner with
an upper-airway obstruction.

904
00:36:16.424 --> 00:36:18.133
Didn't clear
with abdominal thrusts.

905
00:36:18.134 --> 00:36:19.426
We got to take a look.

906
00:36:19.427 --> 00:36:21.761
Heart rate's 118.
Pulse ox 96.

907
00:36:21.762 --> 00:36:23.597
Mr. Mitchell.
we're gonna sedate you

908
00:36:23.598 --> 00:36:25.140
to look down your throat. okay?

909
00:36:25.141 --> 00:36:27.017
Draw up ketamine
and rocuronium.

910
00:36:27.018 --> 00:36:29.436
What about ketamine only?

911
00:36:29.437 --> 00:36:31.313
No. we need full paralysis

912
00:36:31.314 --> 00:36:33.231
for a successful
first-pass intubation.

913
00:36:33.232 --> 00:36:35.817
Might not need an intubation
if it's just a foreign body.

914
00:36:35.818 --> 00:36:37.444
We can't assume that.

915
00:36:37.445 --> 00:36:39.487
It could be subglottic
stenosis. epiglottitis.

916
00:36:39.488 --> 00:36:41.324
I got ketamine and roc.

917
00:36:43.159 --> 00:36:46.119
Ketamine only.
80 milligrams.

918
00:36:46.120 --> 00:36:50.165
In that case. I'll leave this
in your capable hands.

919
00:36:50.166 --> 00:36:54.461
Cetacaine spray
and a Yankauer. please.

920
00:36:54.462 --> 00:36:57.130
30 minutes ago. I told you
I'd never been sued.

921
00:36:57.131 --> 00:36:59.341
I'd like to keep it that way.
- Mm.

922
00:37:01.135 --> 00:37:03.678
Instead of showing up here.
you'd think

923
00:37:03.679 --> 00:37:06.348
he'd put an eight-hour hard-on
to good use.

924
00:37:06.349 --> 00:37:08.475
Well. it is
a medical emergency.

925
00:37:08.476 --> 00:37:10.393
If left untreated.
priapism can cause

926
00:37:10.394 --> 00:37:12.020
permanent damage to the penis

927
00:37:12.021 --> 00:37:13.688
and erectile dysfunction
forever.

928
00:37:13.689 --> 00:37:15.357
Thanks for the PSA.

929
00:37:15.358 --> 00:37:17.150
Pharmacist mixed up
phenylephrine.

930
00:37:17.151 --> 00:37:19.736
10 cc's of 100 mikes per cc.

931
00:37:19.737 --> 00:37:21.154
Great.
That's the maximum dose.

932
00:37:21.155 --> 00:37:22.530
Sterile bolus saline.

933
00:37:22.531 --> 00:37:23.990
You might need to refill

934
00:37:23.991 --> 00:37:25.909
since they'll be
flushing over and over again.

935
00:37:25.910 --> 00:37:28.370
Hold out the empty basin to
catch whatever they pull out.

936
00:37:28.371 --> 00:37:30.330
Got it?
- I think so.

937
00:37:30.331 --> 00:37:31.998
Holler if you need me.

938
00:37:31.999 --> 00:37:34.334
- How we doing?
- Oh. he's out from Versed.

939
00:37:34.335 --> 00:37:36.962
Did a lidocaine block
to the dorsal penile nerves

940
00:37:36.963 --> 00:37:39.089
at 10 and 2.
- Yeah. he's ready.

941
00:37:39.090 --> 00:37:40.799
Excellent.

942
00:37:40.800 --> 00:37:43.802
Enter the dorsal side
to hit the corpus cavernosum.

943
00:37:43.803 --> 00:37:45.011
I'll hold the glans.

944
00:37:45.012 --> 00:37:47.973
- How deep?
- 2 centimeters.

945
00:37:47.974 --> 00:37:49.892
Ah. now aspirate.

946
00:37:52.395 --> 00:37:56.356
You guys do this.
like. every day?

947
00:37:56.357 --> 00:37:58.400
If we're lucky.

948
00:37:58.401 --> 00:37:59.609
Come here.

949
00:38:02.697 --> 00:38:06.032
Okay. let's lay him down
and take a look.

950
00:38:06.033 --> 00:38:07.867
Okay.

951
00:38:14.208 --> 00:38:17.043
Good view of the epiglottis.

952
00:38:17.044 --> 00:38:20.213
And mystery solved.

953
00:38:20.214 --> 00:38:23.425
This is what you get for
eating broccoli for breakfast.

954
00:38:23.426 --> 00:38:25.427
Get a good grip on it.

955
00:38:25.428 --> 00:38:26.470
Okay.

956
00:38:28.431 --> 00:38:30.349
Okay.

957
00:38:35.730 --> 00:38:38.648
I can see why
the Heimlich didn't work.

958
00:38:38.649 --> 00:38:40.526
Rotate a little bit.

959
00:38:43.904 --> 00:38:46.072
Voilà!

960
00:38:46.073 --> 00:38:48.825
That is why you
give ketamine alone.

961
00:38:48.826 --> 00:38:50.452
because if we gave a paralytic.

962
00:38:50.453 --> 00:38:53.705
we would have to intubate
and ventilate for an hour.

963
00:38:55.458 --> 00:38:58.043
All right. this guy is going
to Westbridge for surgery.

964
00:38:58.044 --> 00:39:00.211
Trauma 1 will move out shortly.

965
00:39:00.212 --> 00:39:02.672
And our Alzheimer's widow.
Evelyn Bostick.

966
00:39:02.673 --> 00:39:04.799
can see her husband
in the viewing room.

967
00:39:04.800 --> 00:39:06.343
God bless her.

968
00:39:06.344 --> 00:39:08.470
My CT results back
on Michael Williams?

969
00:39:08.471 --> 00:39:10.472
Not yet--neither are the labs
on our little girl. Kylie.

970
00:39:10.473 --> 00:39:12.015
That's not me.

971
00:39:12.016 --> 00:39:13.933
I did. however.
get a few things back

972
00:39:13.934 --> 00:39:15.268
on our abandoned baby Jane Doe.

973
00:39:15.269 --> 00:39:16.519
Still not me.

974
00:39:16.520 --> 00:39:18.104
I'll take those.

975
00:39:18.105 --> 00:39:20.482
Just keeping you informed.

976
00:39:20.483 --> 00:39:22.359
Yep.

977
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:24.611
Okay.

978
00:39:24.612 --> 00:39:27.864
We're just trying
to get her upstairs.

979
00:39:27.865 --> 00:39:30.450
Okay.
All right. got it.

980
00:39:30.451 --> 00:39:33.620
Superbaby's urine
dipped negative 0 WBCs.

981
00:39:33.621 --> 00:39:35.622
Respiratory panel is positive
for rhinovirus.

982
00:39:35.623 --> 00:39:36.998
giving us a benign source.

983
00:39:36.999 --> 00:39:38.666
Procalcitonin
and CRP are pending.

984
00:39:38.667 --> 00:39:40.752
Now peds is saying
they want a urine tox screen

985
00:39:40.753 --> 00:39:42.837
and an HIV antigen
before they'll take her.

986
00:39:42.838 --> 00:39:44.714
That sounds excessive.

987
00:39:44.715 --> 00:39:46.758
I feel like they're just
trying to keep her down here.

988
00:39:46.759 --> 00:39:48.468
Can you blame them?

989
00:39:48.469 --> 00:39:50.595
Never met a peds nurse yet
that wasn't a little wacky.

990
00:39:50.596 --> 00:39:52.514
You know what 12 hours
of crying babies does

991
00:39:52.515 --> 00:39:53.848
to a person's psyche?

992
00:39:53.849 --> 00:39:55.308
I almost went into peds.

993
00:39:55.309 --> 00:39:56.976
Good thing you didn't.
trust me.

994
00:39:56.977 --> 00:39:59.104
Too long up there.
you're cuckoo for Cocoa Puffs.

995
00:39:59.105 --> 00:40:01.773
- You are very punchy today.
- Punchy's my new baseline.

996
00:40:01.774 --> 00:40:03.942
Anyone even looks at me funny.
I'm taking them out.

997
00:40:03.943 --> 00:40:05.443
going right for the eyes.

998
00:40:05.444 --> 00:40:06.945
I'll eye-gouge you.

999
00:40:06.946 --> 00:40:08.738
Bet you never knew
that about me.

1000
00:40:08.739 --> 00:40:10.407
I did not.

1001
00:40:10.408 --> 00:40:12.325
Where is Dr. Al-Hashimi?
- In North 5 with the priapism.

1002
00:40:12.326 --> 00:40:14.160
Ha!
Better her than me.

1003
00:40:14.161 --> 00:40:16.162
I did not intend for that

1004
00:40:16.163 --> 00:40:18.164
to come off as sexual
in any way.

1005
00:40:18.165 --> 00:40:19.999
And on that note.
I'm gonna go check on Louie.

1006
00:40:20.000 --> 00:40:21.876
and then I'm gonna get
some air in the ambulance bay.

1007
00:40:21.877 --> 00:40:23.753
So if anybody needs me.
that's where I'll be.

1008
00:40:23.754 --> 00:40:25.213
Got it. Cap.

1009
00:40:25.214 --> 00:40:27.924
Ah. ah. ah!

